        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 5:51PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 551 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Twin Butte, or 29 miles southwest of Glenns Ferry, moving north at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Bruneau Canyon Viewpoint around 600 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
